law.text:
Within 5 days after the National Labor Relations Board or other public or private unit certifies or recognizes a bargaining representative, the bargaining representative shall submit to the Mediation Service a report that contains:
notice of the certification or recognition;
the name and address of the employer;
the total number of employees in the business establishment;
the total number of employees in the bargaining unit; and
if known, the date on which negotiations to establish a collective bargaining agreement are to begin.
